.LP
\fINumerical Computation Guide\fR 
.SH NOTES
.sp
.LP
In a multithreaded program, the \fBfex_merge_flags()\fR function affects the floating point environment only for the calling thread.
.sp
.LP
The \fBfex_merge_flags()\fR function automatically installs and deinstalls \fBSIGFPE\fR handlers and sets and clears the trap enable mode bits in the floating point status register as needed.  If a program uses these functions and attempts to install a \fBSIGFPE\fR handler or control the trap enable mode bits independently, the resulting behavior is not defined.
